Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of MAP-inference for undirected discrete graphical models, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The proposed algorithm is based on linear programming relaxation and has practical efficiency, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of graphical models also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
